  "body": "I am using Geth to develop a private chain. Every time I start the Geth Javascript console, the log in its directory will update information like this:\r\n\r\n> geth : INFO [07-09|10:22:36.319] Maximum peer count                       ETH=25 LES=0 total=25\r\n\r\nwhich I take as the allowed size of my chain. **However, the project I am working on involves more than 25 nodes.** How can I modify this default configuration? I have rummaged through the source code on https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum, but don't get much insight into the problem. \r\n\r\nI have tried putting forward this question at https://discord.gg/nthXNEv and at the Ethereum stack exchange at https://ethereum.stackexchange.com but failed due to some unknown error. Please help! @gravityblast @bts @shazow @fjl @sauliusgrigaitis \r\n",
